  • Type Parameters:
    S - the concrete instance of InverseSetLattice

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Lattice<S>
    public abstract class InverseSetLattice<S extends InverseSetLattice<S,​E>,​E>
extends BaseLattice<S>
    A generic inverse set lattice containing a set of elements. Lattice operations are the opposite of the SetLattice ones, namely:
    • the lub is the set intersection
    • the ≤ is the inverse set inclusion
    Widening on instances of this lattice depends on the cardinality of the domain of the underlying elements. The provided implementation behave as the domain is finite, thus invoking the lub. Inverse set lattices defined on infinite domains must implement a coherent widening logic.
